generalfeedback.text:
Worked Solution

  • Prime: is a number greater than 1 with exactly two distinct positive divisors: 1 and itself.
  • Composite: is a number greater than 1 with more than two positive divisors.
  • Neither: Numbers 0 and 1 are neither prime nor composite.

Note that:

  • If a number > 2 ends in 0, 2, 4, 6, or 8, it's composite.
  • If a number > 5 ends in 0 or 5, it's composite.
  • If the sum of digits is divisible by 3, the number is composite.
  • 0 and 1 are neither prime nor composite.
